{
    "response": "To compute the **sample variance** of the data set:\n\n$$\n\\{1, 12, -17, -3, -11, -5\\}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### **Step 1: Find the mean (average) of the data**\n\n$$\n\\text{Mean} = \\frac{1 + 12 + (-17) + (-3) + (-11) + (-5)}{6}\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{1 + 12 - 17 - 3 - 11 - 5}{6}\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{-21}{6} = -3.5\n$$\n\n---\n\n### **Step 2: Compute the squared differences from the mean**\n\nFor each data point $ x_i $, compute $ (x_i - \\text{mean})^2 $:\n\n$$\n\\begin{align*}\n(1 - (-3.5))^2 &= (4.5)^2 = 20.25 \\\\\n(12 - (-3.5))^2 &= (15.5)^2 = 240.25 \\\\\n(-17 - (-3.5))^2 &= (-13.5)^2 = 182.25 \\\\\n(-3 - (-3.5))^2 &= (0.5)^2 = 0.25 \\\\\n(-11 - (-3.5))^2 &= (-7.5)^2 = 56.25 \\\\\n(-5 - (-3.5))^2 &= (-1.5)^2 = 2.25 \\\\\n\\end{align*}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### **Step 3: Sum the squared differences**\n\n$$\n20.25 + 240.25 + 182.25 + 0.25 + 56.25 + 2.25 = 511.5\n$$\n\n---\n\n### **Step 4: Divide by $ n - 1 $ (sample variance formula)**\n\n$$\n\\text{Sample Variance} = \\frac{511.5}{6 - 1} = \\frac{511.5}{5} = \\boxed{102.3}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### \u2705 Final Answer:\n\n$$\n\\boxed{102.3}\n$$"
